  "prompt": "How can I stop my stammering?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help manage stammering:\n\n1. Speech Therapy\n- Work with a professional speech therapist\n- Learn specific techniques to control speech flow\n- Practice speech exercises\n\n2. Breathing Techniques\n- Practice deep, controlled breathing\n- Use diaphragmatic breathing exercises\n- Slow down your speech rate\n\n3. Relaxation Methods\n- Practice meditation\n- Reduce stress and anxiety\n- Use relaxation techniques like progressive muscle relaxation\n\n4. Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT)\n- Address underlying psychological factors\n- Build confidence\n- Manage anxiety related to speaking\n\n5. Practice Speaking\n- Start with low-pressure situations\n- Read aloud\n- Practice speaking in front of a mirror\n- Join support groups\n\n6. Vocal Techniques\n- Speak slowly and smoothly\n- Use gentle onset of sounds\n- Practice smooth transitions between words\n\n7. Additional Tips\n- Avoid finishing sentences for yourself\n- Don't rush while speaking\n- Focus on communication, not perfection\n- Use visualization techniques\n\n8. Medical Consultation\n- Consult a speech pathologist\n- Consider potential medical treatments\n- Rule out underlying neurological conditions\n\nRemember, managing stammering is a gradual process requiring patience and consistent practice.",
